            content:
                '---\nname: drawio\ntitle: Draw.io Diagrams\nversion: 2.0.0\ndescription: >\n  Read, interpret, review, AND build or modify `.drawio` (mxGraph Extensible Markup Language (XML))\n  diagram files in a repository. Reading: parse structure, identify components and connections, trace\n  flow, and explain what a diagram depicts or what changed. Building: generate or edit well-formed\n  mxGraph XML from a description, apply consistent style presets, validate it, and produce a\n  shareable/embeddable artifact. Use when a `.drawio` file must be understood, a Pull Request (PR)\n  changes one, architecture/flow must be extracted from one, OR the user asks to create/update a\n  `.drawio` diagram. Boundaries: for Mermaid (text-based) diagrams defer to the mermaid skill; for the\n  documentation a diagram lives in, defer to project-documentation. Never invents structure when\n  reading; always validates well-formedness when writing.\ntags: [drawio, diagrams, mxgraph, xml, architecture, flowchart, build, modify, review, visualization]\nallowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob, Write, Edit, Bash\nreferences:\n  - references/diagram-types.md\n  - references/style-presets.md\n  - references/style-extraction.md\n  - references/troubleshooting.md\nscripts:\n  - scripts/validate-drawio.py\n  - scripts/encode_drawio_url.py\n  - scripts/repair_png.py\nassets:\n  - styles/schema.json\n  - styles/built-in/default.json\n  - styles/built-in/corporate.json\n  - styles/built-in/handdrawn.json\n# related-skills are OPTIONAL pointers only — this skill never requires another to function.\nrelated-skills:\n  - mermaid: optional — text-based Mermaid diagrams instead of mxGraph XML\n  - project-documentation: optional — may interpret/embed `.drawio` diagrams in docs (neither skill requires the other)\ninstall:\n  defaultLocation: .claude/skills/drawio/\n  supportsProject: true\n  supportsGlobal: true\n---\n\n# Draw.io Diagrams\n\nYou read, explain, and build `.drawio` (mxGraph Extensible Markup Language) diagrams. You parse and\ninterpret existing diagrams accurately, and you generate or modify well-formed diagrams on request.\n\n## When to use\n\n- **Read / review:** a `.drawio` file must be understood; a Pull Request changes one; architecture or\n  flow must be extracted for documentation.\n- **Build / modify:** the user asks to create a new `.drawio` diagram or update an existing one.\n\n## Draw.io XML structure (essentials)\n\n```xml\n<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>\n<mxfile host="drawio" version="26.0.0">\n  <diagram name="Page-1">\n    <mxGraphModel>\n      <root>\n        <mxCell id="0" />\n        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />\n        <!-- user shapes start at id="2" -->\n      </root>\n    </mxGraphModel>\n  </diagram>\n</mxfile>\n```\n\n- `id="0"` and `id="1"` are required root cells — always present.\n- User shapes start at `id="2"` and increment; each has `parent="1"` unless inside a container (then\n  `parent` = the container\'s id, with geometry relative to the parent).\n- `<mxfile>` may contain multiple `<diagram>` elements (multi-page); each is its own model/tree.\n- Vertex cells (`vertex="1"`) are shapes; edge cells (`edge="1"`) connect shapes via `source`/`target`\n  attributes that reference cell ids.\n\nRead `references/diagram-types.md` for shape/style vocabulary per diagram type.\n\n## Workflow — Reading / Reviewing\n\n1. **Locate & open** the `.drawio` file(s). Detect raw `<mxGraphModel>` XML vs. a compressed/encoded\n   `<diagram>` string (deflate + base64); if encoded, state it must be decoded first (do not guess).\n2. **Identify pages** (`<diagram>` elements), then **inventory components** (vertex cells — label\n   `value`, type from `style`) and **map connections** (edge cells — resolve `source`/`target` to\n   labels, note edge labels).\n3. **Identify containers / groups** (`swimlane`, `group`, `container=1`).\n4. **Describe the flow & layout**; **flag issues** if reviewing (orphaned nodes, dangling edges,\n   overlapping shapes, inconsistent styling — see `references/troubleshooting.md`).\n\n## Workflow — Building / Modifying\n\n1. **Pick the diagram type** and load its conventions from `references/diagram-types.md`.\n2. **Choose a style preset** from `styles/built-in/*.json` (validated against `styles/schema.json`);\n   read `references/style-presets.md` for the color/shape/edge conventions and how to apply a preset.\n   To learn a preset from an existing file or image, read `references/style-extraction.md`.\n3. **Generate the mxGraph XML:** root cells `id="0"`/`id="1"`; user shapes from `id="2"`; geometry per\n   shape; edges with `source`/`target`; containers via `parent`. Encode special characters in `value`\n   attributes with XML entities (`&amp;` `&lt;` `&gt;` `&quot;`) and use `&#xa;` for line breaks.\n4. **Validate** with `scripts/validate-drawio.py` — well-formed XML, matched cells, every edge\'s\n   `source`/`target` resolves, no orphaned cells. Fix everything it reports.\n5. **Produce the artifact:** write the `.drawio` file; when a shareable link is wanted run\n   `scripts/encode_drawio_url.py`; after a draw.io `-e` PNG export run `scripts/repair_png.py` so the\n   PNG opens in viewers and keeps the editable source embedded.\n\n```bash\npython3 scripts/validate-drawio.py path/to/diagram.drawio\npython3 scripts/encode_drawio_url.py path/to/diagram.drawio   # prints a viewer URL\npython3 scripts/repair_png.py path/to/diagram.drawio.png      # idempotent PNG repair\n```\n\n## Mandatory validation (before answering / writing)\n\n- [ ] **Reading:** every described component/connection exists in the file; `source`/`target`\n      identifiers resolved to real labels; encoded-content case handled explicitly; no file modified.\n- [ ] **Building:** `scripts/validate-drawio.py` passed (well-formed, matched cells, resolvable edges);\n      the chosen style preset validates against the schema; no orphaned/dangling cells.\n- [ ] No invented structure (reading) and no broken XML emitted (building).\n\n## Output format & location\n\n- **Reading:** a structured interpretation — pages · components · connections · containers · flow ·\n  issues. End with `DRAWIO_READ_COMPLETE`.\n- **Building:** the written `.drawio` file path (+ shareable URL / repaired PNG if requested) and a\n  short summary of what was created/changed. End with `DRAWIO_BUILD_COMPLETE`.\n\n## Gotchas\n\n- `id="0"`/`id="1"` are root cells; user shapes start at `id="2"`. Children use `parent="<containerId>"`\n  with geometry relative to the parent.\n- Compressed diagrams (deflate + base64) can\'t be read without decoding — say so rather than guessing.\n- Self-closing edge cells (`<mxCell ... edge="1" />`) won\'t render — use the expanded form with a\n  `<mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry" />` child.\n- Keep `source`/`target` pointing at existing cell ids — dangling references break rendering.\n- Don\'t infer meaning from color alone; confirm against labels/structure.\n',
